1
00:00:01,262 --> 00:00:04,656
♪ Have a holly jolly Christmas

2
00:00:04,700 --> 00:00:09,400
♪ It's the best time
of the year... ♪

3
00:00:09,444 --> 00:00:11,837
Will they run out
before we get in there?

4
00:00:11,881 --> 00:00:14,318
No. We'll get him
a robot, then.

5
00:00:14,362 --> 00:00:16,842
A six-year-old really
doesn't need a drone anyway.

6
00:00:16,886 --> 00:00:18,453
I know, but I promised him.

7
00:00:18,496 --> 00:00:20,933
It'll be fine, all right?
They're not gonna run out.

8
00:00:20,977 --> 00:00:22,892
♪ When you walk
down the street ♪

9
00:00:22,935 --> 00:00:24,676
And we're okay
money-wise?

10
00:00:24,720 --> 00:00:27,244
I already told you,
I can swing it.

11
00:00:27,288 --> 00:00:29,072
I'll put my half
on a credit card.

12
00:00:29,116 --> 00:00:30,856
Yeah, just keep walking.
You'll see me.

13
00:00:30,900 --> 00:00:32,075
Will you be able

14
00:00:32,119 --> 00:00:33,250
to pay his child support?

15
00:00:33,294 --> 00:00:34,556
I really count on that.

16
00:00:34,599 --> 00:00:37,559
Like I said, next week,
soon as I get paid.

17
00:00:37,602 --> 00:00:39,735
♪ Somebody waits for you...

18
00:00:39,778 --> 00:00:41,432
I'm sorry.

19
00:00:41,476 --> 00:00:43,434
I know you're trying.

20
00:00:43,478 --> 00:00:45,088
[man chuckles]

21
00:00:45,132 --> 00:00:47,090
Here we are.What took you
so long?

22
00:00:47,134 --> 00:00:49,875
Oh, we had to wait
for Thanksgiving dinner to end.

23
00:00:49,919 --> 00:00:52,400
I had to find a bar.
Had to close a bar.

24
00:00:52,443 --> 00:00:54,489
Excuse me. We've
been waiting out here

25
00:00:54,532 --> 00:00:57,100
for over four hours.Okay. So have I.

26
00:00:57,144 --> 00:00:58,493
Your friends haven't.Okay, hey, come on.

27
00:00:58,536 --> 00:01:00,016
Everyone's gonna get in.That's not the point.

28
00:01:00,060 --> 00:01:04,194
I just told you, I've been here,
saving their place.

29
00:01:04,238 --> 00:01:05,978
There's no saving places.
Your friends could get

30
00:01:06,022 --> 00:01:07,371
to the back of the line

31
00:01:07,415 --> 00:01:09,199
and wait their turn,
just like everybody else!

32
00:01:09,243 --> 00:01:10,896
First of all,
lower your voice.

33
00:01:10,940 --> 00:01:12,463
Second of all,
it's three people.

34
00:01:12,507 --> 00:01:14,552
And third of all,
it's the holidays.

35
00:01:14,596 --> 00:01:16,337
Let's keep it festive,
Cruella de Vil.

36
00:01:16,380 --> 00:01:19,209
Hey. That's my wife
you're talking to, all right?

37
00:01:19,253 --> 00:01:20,863
Oh, you have
my deepest sympathies.

38
00:01:20,906 --> 00:01:22,908
[men chuckling]

39
00:01:24,823 --> 00:01:27,130
[men grunting, laughing]

40
00:01:27,174 --> 00:01:29,872
MAN [mocking]:
Oh, sorry.

41
00:01:29,915 --> 00:01:33,180
Security! Help!
Police? Security?

42
00:01:33,223 --> 00:01:34,572
Someone!And take

43
00:01:34,616 --> 00:01:37,532
your ugly wife with you.

44
00:01:37,575 --> 00:01:41,057
Whoa, whoa, whoa, whoa.
Hey, that's going on here?

45
00:01:41,101 --> 00:01:42,972
Officer,
I'm so glad to see you.

46
00:01:43,015 --> 00:01:44,800
I was just standing in line,
minding my business.

47
00:01:44,843 --> 00:01:46,802
He's lying.
He punched my husband,

48
00:01:46,845 --> 00:01:48,195
and they all
ganged up on him.

49
00:01:48,238 --> 00:01:51,154
Which one's your husband?
You okay?

50
00:01:51,198 --> 00:01:53,461
Guy hit me in the head.Say what?!

51
00:01:53,504 --> 00:01:55,115
I'm the one on the ground.

52
00:01:55,158 --> 00:01:56,203
This man is a menace,
and the wife...

53
00:01:56,246 --> 00:01:58,509
Hey, all right.
You, get up

54
00:01:58,553 --> 00:01:59,641
I'm calling for a wagon.

55
00:01:59,684 --> 00:02:01,208
You clowns can
discuss this in court.

56
00:02:01,251 --> 00:02:03,340
Oh...
What?What?

57
00:02:03,384 --> 00:02:05,560
They came at me,man.Hey. You're all under arrest.

58
00:02:05,603 --> 00:02:08,128
Oh, come on, dude.

59
00:02:12,567 --> 00:02:15,004
I'm Cassandra Bennet,
your public defender.

60
00:02:15,047 --> 00:02:17,528
Looks like your co-defendants
hired private attorneys.

61
00:02:17,572 --> 00:02:19,835
They've been released.They're not
my co-defendants.

62
00:02:19,878 --> 00:02:21,402
The prosecutor's
asking for bail.

63
00:02:21,445 --> 00:02:23,839
Bail? Come on, I was
the one who was attacked.

64
00:02:23,882 --> 00:02:25,580
I didn't do anything.

65
00:02:25,623 --> 00:02:28,452
Your intake says you're
from outside the jurisdiction.

66
00:02:28,496 --> 00:02:29,627
Where do you live?

67
00:02:29,671 --> 00:02:32,152
Philly.
My wife lives here.

68
00:02:32,195 --> 00:02:33,501
Separated.

69
00:02:33,544 --> 00:02:35,329
You have four defaults
on your record,

70
00:02:35,372 --> 00:02:37,069
all drunk and disorderlies.Come on.

71
00:02:37,113 --> 00:02:38,549
Those are from a long time ago.

72
00:02:38,593 --> 00:02:40,986
Before I was married.
Before I had a kid.

73
00:02:41,030 --> 00:02:42,597
I'm six months sober.

74
00:02:42,640 --> 00:02:43,815
D.A.'s saying you're
a flight risk.

75
00:02:43,859 --> 00:02:46,514
He's asking for bail.
$5,000 cash.

76
00:02:46,557 --> 00:02:49,560
I don't have that kind of money.

77
00:02:49,604 --> 00:02:51,475
And I have to be
at work Monday morning.

78
00:02:51,519 --> 00:02:53,695
Can your wife help?

79
00:02:56,001 --> 00:02:59,483
No, look, if I'm not at work
I'm gonna lose my job.

80
00:02:59,527 --> 00:03:02,660
And if I lose my job...So, what's it gonna be?

81
00:03:02,704 --> 00:03:05,794
The D.A.'s offering a deal.
Plead guilty to simple assault,

82
00:03:05,837 --> 00:03:08,188
admit you pushed the guy,
you'll get a $75 fine

83
00:03:08,231 --> 00:03:09,754
and community service.

84
00:03:09,798 --> 00:03:12,235
That's...

85
00:03:12,279 --> 00:03:14,585
Wait a second,
that-that's not fair.

86
00:03:14,629 --> 00:03:16,631
What do you--
I was surrounded.

87
00:03:16,674 --> 00:03:19,155
There was four of them,
there was one of me.

88
00:03:19,199 --> 00:03:20,939
I didn't start it.
The guy punched mein the face.

89
00:03:20,983 --> 00:03:22,898
The cops said the other guy
was on the ground.

90
00:03:22,941 --> 00:03:24,769
He was drunk.

91
00:03:24,813 --> 00:03:26,728
I gave him a shove
to keep him away from me.

92
00:03:26,771 --> 00:03:28,599
Don't I get
to tell someone that?

93
00:03:28,643 --> 00:03:31,602
Don't I get to tell a judge?Sure. Monday.

94
00:03:31,646 --> 00:03:33,169
I have to come back Monday?

95
00:03:33,213 --> 00:03:34,344
No, you don't have
to come back.

96
00:03:34,388 --> 00:03:36,999
You're going to be
in jail until then, okay?

97
00:03:37,042 --> 00:03:40,089
Or you can pay the bail,
or you can take this deal.

98
00:03:40,132 --> 00:03:41,351
Oh...

99
00:03:41,395 --> 00:03:43,571
Sir, can I help you with this?

100
00:03:43,614 --> 00:03:47,749
It's a misdemeanor.
It's $75.

101
00:03:47,792 --> 00:03:50,012
They'll transfer your
community service to Philly.

102
00:03:50,055 --> 00:03:52,449
This will have absolutely
no impact on your life

103
00:03:52,493 --> 00:03:53,885
going forward.

104
00:03:53,929 --> 00:03:56,105
You'll be able to spend
the weekend with your family

105
00:03:56,148 --> 00:03:57,715
and you'll be back at work
on Monday.

106
00:03:57,759 --> 00:04:01,023
$75.

107
00:04:01,066 --> 00:04:02,546
Deal's off the table
in 60 seconds.

108
00:04:02,590 --> 00:04:04,287
Okay, fine. I'll take the deal.

109
00:04:04,331 --> 00:04:06,768
Plead guilty.

110
00:04:09,553 --> 00:04:11,555
["It's the Most Wonderful Time
of the Year" playing]

111
00:04:19,911 --> 00:04:22,566
♪ There'll be scary
ghost stories... ♪

112
00:04:22,610 --> 00:04:23,959
What can I do for you?

113
00:04:24,002 --> 00:04:26,483
Chris Coleman.Yes.

114
00:04:26,527 --> 00:04:28,355
You pled guilty to assault
last week in New York?

115
00:04:28,398 --> 00:04:31,445
[sighs]
Yeah. So? What's this about?

116
00:04:31,488 --> 00:04:33,621
The guy that you assaulted...I didn't assault anyone.

117
00:04:33,664 --> 00:04:35,666
He went into a coma
two nights ago.

118
00:04:35,710 --> 00:04:37,625
Result of the head injury
you inflicted upon him

119
00:04:37,668 --> 00:04:38,887
when you assaulted him.

120
00:04:38,930 --> 00:04:40,584
He died this morning.

121
00:04:40,628 --> 00:04:42,717
You're being charged
with manslaughter.

122
00:04:42,760 --> 00:04:43,935
Hands behind
your back, sir.

123
00:04:43,979 --> 00:04:47,156
♪ It's the most wonderful time

124
00:04:47,199 --> 00:04:49,898
♪ Of the year.

125
00:04:49,941 --> 00:04:53,684
Ah, look, Ms. Bennet, you've got
to ease up on yourself.

126
00:04:53,728 --> 00:04:55,338
There's no way
you could have known

127
00:04:55,382 --> 00:04:58,559
that a run-of-the-mill plea
would go sideways like that.

128
00:04:58,602 --> 00:05:01,779
Yeah, but I was the one
who told him to take the deal.

129
00:05:01,823 --> 00:05:03,564
Now he's sitting in a cell
at Rikers

130
00:05:03,607 --> 00:05:05,479
staring at 20 years.

131
00:05:05,522 --> 00:05:07,568
If only he'd waited
and gone to trial,

132
00:05:07,611 --> 00:05:09,961
he almost certainly would have
been found not guilty.

133
00:05:10,005 --> 00:05:13,748
Well, first of all,
he couldn't make bail,

134
00:05:13,791 --> 00:05:15,010
so that's not on you.

135
00:05:15,053 --> 00:05:17,795
Second of all,
every lawyer in your office

136
00:05:17,839 --> 00:05:19,667
would have done the same thing.

137
00:05:19,710 --> 00:05:21,756
Strike that.
Every lawyer in your office

138
00:05:21,799 --> 00:05:23,801
hasdone the same thing.

139
00:05:23,845 --> 00:05:26,195
I did it when I was an A.D.A.

140
00:05:26,238 --> 00:05:28,502
Look, I know I barely know you.

141
00:05:28,545 --> 00:05:31,679
I know I'm just this
young public defender

142
00:05:31,722 --> 00:05:33,942
you and your boss make
mincemeat out of

143
00:05:33,985 --> 00:05:37,641
in the courtroom, but I could
really use some help.

144
00:05:37,685 --> 00:05:39,774
What are you talking about?

145
00:05:39,817 --> 00:05:41,036
Well, he's got
no money.

146
00:05:41,079 --> 00:05:44,082
No money.
He's got a wife and a kid.

147
00:05:44,126 --> 00:05:48,086
And he's already pleaded guilty.

148
00:05:48,130 --> 00:05:50,306
He is going to lose.

149
00:05:50,350 --> 00:05:51,655
Unless he gets
some high-powered help,

150
00:05:51,699 --> 00:05:54,092
he is going to lose.

151
00:05:54,136 --> 00:05:56,704
Well, aren't you
high-powered enough?

152
00:05:56,747 --> 00:06:00,577
Mr. Colón, I've been
doing this for 18 months.

153
00:06:00,621 --> 00:06:02,318
I like to think
I'm really smart.

154
00:06:02,362 --> 00:06:04,799
Smart enough to know
when I'm just not smart enough.

155
00:06:04,842 --> 00:06:08,672
I know you and your firm
do pro bono work. I-I-I promise

156
00:06:08,716 --> 00:06:10,370
I will do all the heavy lifting.

157
00:06:10,413 --> 00:06:12,197
You guys wouldn't even
have to go to court.

158
00:06:12,241 --> 00:06:15,418
If I could just
check in about strategy,

159
00:06:15,462 --> 00:06:19,553
maybe get you to make
an appearance at voir dire.

160
00:06:19,596 --> 00:06:21,729
Guy's facing 20 years
for something he didn't do,

161
00:06:21,772 --> 00:06:23,339
pled guilty for
expediency's sake,

162
00:06:23,383 --> 00:06:25,907
and now he's caught up in
the system and he can't get out.

163
00:06:25,950 --> 00:06:28,300
Sounds like something
out of Kafka.
Exactly.

164
00:06:28,344 --> 00:06:29,954
So who's the
public defender?

165
00:06:29,998 --> 00:06:31,826
Oh, she's a kid.

166
00:06:31,869 --> 00:06:34,176
I think she sat third chair
against us a couple of times.

167
00:06:34,219 --> 00:06:37,222
Kind of reminds me
of me at that age.

168
00:06:37,266 --> 00:06:39,703
Look, we won't even
have to go to court.

169
00:06:39,747 --> 00:06:42,053
She just wants us to weigh in
on some strategy,

170
00:06:42,097 --> 00:06:44,404
maybe show up for voir dire.

171
00:06:44,447 --> 00:06:46,362
So what do you think?

172
00:06:46,406 --> 00:06:48,712
And keep in mind
it's the holiday season.

173
00:06:48,756 --> 00:06:50,932
Oh, it's okay, I'm already
on the naughty list.

174
00:06:50,975 --> 00:06:53,021
[elevator bell chimes]
Sure.

175
00:06:53,064 --> 00:06:54,849
If we don't really
have to do anything.

176
00:06:54,892 --> 00:06:56,938
Oh, a-and any way that I
could set up a meeting

177
00:06:56,981 --> 00:06:58,940
between you and the A.D.A.?

178
00:06:58,983 --> 00:07:01,682
See if maybe you could
sweet talk this ambitious punk

179
00:07:01,725 --> 00:07:03,292
into dropping the charges?

180
00:07:03,335 --> 00:07:06,904
Mm-hmm. What happened to "we
don't even have to go to court"?

181
00:07:06,948 --> 00:07:08,384
Well, w-we don't.

182
00:07:08,428 --> 00:07:11,387
I figured, if you powwow
with the A.D.A.

183
00:07:11,431 --> 00:07:12,867
and he drops the case,

184
00:07:12,910 --> 00:07:15,391
then we really
don't have to go to court.

185
00:07:16,784 --> 00:07:19,221
Let go of the door
and let's consider it

186
00:07:19,264 --> 00:07:21,179
your early Christmas present.

187
00:07:21,223 --> 00:07:24,313
Ah, Bull, you shouldn't have.[elevator bell chimes]

188
00:07:24,356 --> 00:07:26,794
You're preaching
to the choir, pal.

189
00:07:29,492 --> 00:07:30,624
A.D.A. Russo?

190
00:07:30,667 --> 00:07:32,713
Forgive me for
barging in unannounced.

191
00:07:32,756 --> 00:07:34,889
My name's Dr. Jason Bull, and
I'm working with Chris Coleman.

192
00:07:34,932 --> 00:07:35,933
You have a minute?

193
00:07:37,979 --> 00:07:41,069
Dr. Bull. I know who you are.

194
00:07:41,112 --> 00:07:43,158
Uh,

195
00:07:43,201 --> 00:07:45,987
welcome to misdemeanor row.
I'd tell you to pull up a chair,

196
00:07:46,030 --> 00:07:47,989
but that would assume
you brought one with you.

197
00:07:48,032 --> 00:07:49,207
You want mine?

198
00:07:49,251 --> 00:07:51,819
No, I'm good right here. Thanks.

199
00:07:51,862 --> 00:07:53,734
Wow.

200
00:07:53,777 --> 00:07:56,214
It's the kind of office you
work like hell to get out of.

201
00:07:56,258 --> 00:07:58,608
You guys into fantasy football?

202
00:07:58,652 --> 00:08:01,045
Yup.

203
00:08:01,089 --> 00:08:03,874
Uh, what-what can I do
for you, Dr. Bull?

204
00:08:03,918 --> 00:08:05,963
I know you didn't come
all this way to, uh,

205
00:08:06,007 --> 00:08:07,835
check out the office, did you?

206
00:08:07,878 --> 00:08:11,316
I was hoping to get you to drop
the charges against my client.

207
00:08:11,360 --> 00:08:13,797
Why would I do that?

208
00:08:13,841 --> 00:08:16,626
Because the only thing
he's guilty of is bad luck.

209
00:08:16,670 --> 00:08:19,368
Well, that is your opinion,

210
00:08:19,411 --> 00:08:21,544
and you're entitled
to it, certainly.

211
00:08:21,588 --> 00:08:24,939
But from my vantage point,
from the city's vantage point,

212
00:08:24,982 --> 00:08:26,331
he laid his hands on a guy

213
00:08:26,375 --> 00:08:28,159
and that guy
subsequently died.

214
00:08:28,203 --> 00:08:31,728
Mm, not exactly.

215
00:08:31,772 --> 00:08:34,905
We both know if my client
had had $5,000 for bail,

216
00:08:34,949 --> 00:08:36,298
he wouldn't be
in this situation.

217
00:08:36,341 --> 00:08:38,996
He'd still be facing
manslaughter charges.

218
00:08:39,040 --> 00:08:40,563
No, he wouldn't.

219
00:08:40,607 --> 00:08:42,957
He wouldn't have pled guilty,
he would've pled innocent,

220
00:08:43,000 --> 00:08:44,306
which is what he is.

221
00:08:44,349 --> 00:08:46,003
And then he would've
explained to a jury that,

222
00:08:46,047 --> 00:08:47,004
when he was
attacked, all he did

223
00:08:47,048 --> 00:08:49,920
was protect himself.

224
00:08:49,964 --> 00:08:51,400
The truth is, his guilty plea

225
00:08:51,443 --> 00:08:53,445
is the only piece of evidence
you have against him.

226
00:08:53,489 --> 00:08:56,057
Well, the good news is,
if he is innocent,

227
00:08:56,100 --> 00:09:00,017
as you say he is, uh,
a jury will acquit him.

228
00:09:00,061 --> 00:09:04,065
I'm guessing this
your first felony trial.

229
00:09:06,371 --> 00:09:08,330
Everybody has their first,
Dr. Bull.

230
00:09:08,373 --> 00:09:10,941
Absolutely.
Everybody has a first.

231
00:09:10,985 --> 00:09:13,030
The important thing is,
once you get your shot,

232
00:09:13,074 --> 00:09:14,205
you don't want to lose.

233
00:09:14,249 --> 00:09:17,078
Oh, I'm not worried.

234
00:09:17,121 --> 00:09:20,690
See, I have three witnesses and
a dead body and a guilty plea,

235
00:09:20,734 --> 00:09:23,911
so I'm feeling pretty good.

236
00:09:23,954 --> 00:09:27,175
Excellent.
I can't even begin to tell you

237
00:09:27,218 --> 00:09:28,872
how important
your feelings are to me.

238
00:09:30,787 --> 00:09:34,008
See you in court, Mr. Russo.

239
00:09:34,051 --> 00:09:36,706
See you in court,
Dr. Bull.

240
00:09:38,665 --> 00:09:40,623
♪

241
00:09:50,633 --> 00:09:51,939
Good morning, sir.

242
00:09:51,982 --> 00:09:55,551
First day of court.
Beginning of voir dire.

243
00:09:55,595 --> 00:09:58,772
Always my favorite.

244
00:09:58,815 --> 00:10:03,472
Little something
we need to do first.

245
00:10:03,515 --> 00:10:06,518
Oh...

246
00:10:06,562 --> 00:10:10,000
We're gonna throw that
poor girl under the bus?

247
00:10:10,044 --> 00:10:12,916
I don't see that
we have much choice.

248
00:10:14,962 --> 00:10:17,355
Well, we always
have a choice.

