00:38:21,168 --> 00:38:23,866
What-what,
do they know?

875
00:38:23,910 --> 00:38:26,956
Are-are they certain that the,
that the brain injury

876
00:38:27,000 --> 00:38:29,524
was a result of the fall
he took that night?

877
00:38:29,568 --> 00:38:32,484
I haven't seen any
evidence of that,

878
00:38:32,527 --> 00:38:35,095
but-but let's give them
the benefit of a doubt.

879
00:38:35,138 --> 00:38:37,358
My client didn't-didn't
trip him.

880
00:38:37,402 --> 00:38:40,535
My client didn't push him
to the ground.

881
00:38:40,579 --> 00:38:42,363
So why did he fall?

882
00:38:42,407 --> 00:38:46,933
Was it perhaps because, uh,
he drank too much?

883
00:38:46,976 --> 00:38:50,980
Was it perhaps because
the sidewalk was uneven?

884
00:38:51,024 --> 00:38:53,809
Did he have a trick ankle?

885
00:38:53,853 --> 00:38:55,985
Of course, none of these things

886
00:38:56,029 --> 00:38:58,771
have anything to do
with my client.

887
00:38:58,814 --> 00:39:01,774
So why is
my client here?

888
00:39:01,817 --> 00:39:05,473
Well, because he-he
decided to plead guilty

889
00:39:05,517 --> 00:39:09,651
to make it easy for everyone,
including himself, to get home?

890
00:39:09,695 --> 00:39:12,524
Because an ambitious prosecutor

891
00:39:12,567 --> 00:39:16,092
thinks that convicting
somebody, anybody,

892
00:39:16,136 --> 00:39:17,442
will be good
for his career?

893
00:39:17,485 --> 00:39:19,661
Wha... [stammers]

894
00:39:19,705 --> 00:39:21,663
Because, uh-uh,
the world

895
00:39:21,707 --> 00:39:24,840
needs to be saved from, uh, dads

896
00:39:24,884 --> 00:39:27,539
trying to find good deals on
Christmas gifts for their kids?

897
00:39:27,582 --> 00:39:30,455
Well, the point is,

898
00:39:30,498 --> 00:39:33,414
any one of us could've been

899
00:39:33,458 --> 00:39:35,938
standing in that line
that night.

900
00:39:35,982 --> 00:39:39,812
Any one of us here.

901
00:39:39,855 --> 00:39:42,205
Now staring at 20 years
in prison.

902
00:39:45,905 --> 00:39:48,429
Still nothing.

903
00:39:48,473 --> 00:39:51,693
I don't hear a thing.

904
00:39:51,737 --> 00:39:54,174
I guess it's because
I have no idea

905
00:39:54,217 --> 00:39:57,264
what this man
is actually guilty of.

906
00:39:57,307 --> 00:39:59,309
Thank you.

907
00:40:01,181 --> 00:40:02,530
CHRIS:
So now we wait.

908
00:40:02,574 --> 00:40:05,490
So now we wait.

909
00:40:09,755 --> 00:40:11,713
Thank you for those words.

910
00:40:11,757 --> 00:40:14,368
And, uh,

911
00:40:14,412 --> 00:40:17,415
thank you for
saying it that way.

912
00:40:22,507 --> 00:40:24,857
How'd you feel if I came out
to the prison next week?

913
00:40:24,900 --> 00:40:26,336
Just to visit.

914
00:40:27,816 --> 00:40:29,514
Sure.
Yeah.

915
00:40:29,557 --> 00:40:31,559
And with the holidays coming up,

916
00:40:31,603 --> 00:40:34,736
I'll arrange for your wife
and son to come see you.

917
00:40:34,780 --> 00:40:36,172
You're okay with that, right?

918
00:40:36,216 --> 00:40:39,611
Yeah, that'd be great.

